A nation united for healthy youth and communities

The federal Interagency Coordinating Committee on the Prevention of Underage Drinking is working with governments and organizations at the state, territory, and local levels to reduce and prevent underage drinking and its consequences.

Learn More

Report to Congress

Learn more about the prevalence and consequences of underage drinking and ongoing national and state prevention efforts. More

2017 National Survey on Drug Use and Health

Latest National Survey on Drug Use and Health shows progress in reducing teen alcohol use. More

Surgeon General's Report Dedicated to Substance Use Disorders

The 2016 Surgeon General's Report is the first report to be dedicated to substance misuse and related disorders. More

Data

The data provide information on the prevalence, trends, and consequences of underage drinking.

The different agencies also provide related statistics that highlight different health and societal aspects of underage drinking. More

Understanding the Issue

Factors Affecting Underage Drinking is a developmental and environmental context for understanding aimed at reducing a young person's risk of using alcohol or increasing factors that help protect them against alcohol use. More

Prevention/Intervention

Learn more about effective prevention strategies to reduce underage alcohol access, use, and consequences.

Find intervention tools, resources, and services to help young people recover from and avoid alcohol use. More

SEE ALL

ICCPUD News

  • Do colleges adopt effective alcohol use prevention policies?
  • Do state policies to prevent alcohol use during pregnancy work?
  • Social stress and alcohol initiation in adolescent girls
  • How do perceptions of close peers’ drinking behavior affect college students?

  • Monthly Highlights

    April is Alcohol Awareness Month.

    Learn more about increasing awareness and understanding of alcohol addiction, its causes, effective treatment, and recovery.

  • Monthly Highlights

    Get resources to talk with kids about alcohol and drugs.

    Download free resources from the Talk. They Hear You. campaign for tips on talking about alcohol and other drugs with kids.

  • Monthly Highlights

    Watch NIDA’s new video on teen brain development.

    Explore the intriguing similarities between the processes of brain development and computer programming.

  • Monthly Highlights

    Watch the latest NPW webinar on e-cigarettes.

    Understand challenges in youth e-cigarette prevention, evidence-based tools and resources, recent data trends, and strategies for curbing e-cigarette use among youth.

The Communities Talk: Town Hall Meetings to Prevent Underage Drinking initiative educates communities about underage and high-risk drinking and mobilizes them to take evidence-based actions at local, state, and national levels.

About Us

StopAlcoholAbuse.gov is the web portal for the Interagency Coordinating Committee on the Prevention of Underage Drinking (ICCPUD) and your gateway to comprehensive research and resources on prevention.
